4. [discipline:default] [project/turn-state-sentinel-file]
   Turn-state file .gm/turn-state.json (written by prompt-submit-hook at user turn start) tracks {turnId, firstToolFired, execCallsSinceMemorize, recallFiredThisTurn} for per-turn compliance. Pre-tool-use-hook hard-blocks when execCallsSinceMemorize >= 3 unless .gm/no-memorize-this-turn exists. Block can be bypassed by writing sentinel with reason, resets next user turn.
5. [discipline:default] [project/shared-memory-tracked]
   `.gm/rs-learn.db` and `.code-search/` are intentionally tracked (not gitignored) across gm and all downstream repos. These dirs hold rs-learn episodes, community summaries, and rs-codeinsight chunk indices shared across machines, sessions, and CI clones. Parent-dir `.gm/` cannot be wholly ignored (gitignore re-inclusion impossible), so gm enumerates only volatile `.gm/*` files between markers in `…

